The paper deals with the rank weight hierarchy of cyclic codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and algebraic coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves characterizing and deriving bounds for certain classes of cyclic codes, which could fall under graph theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses a refinement of the Singleton bound, which is a well-known result in coding theory and could be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI).
